    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Fellowship is strong and can get set up fast, with lots of possessions. First site denies Aragorn and pulls Legsie. Eomer is the main fighter, Elite Riders are strong, but can be sacrificed. Legolas also. Boromir exerts for Eomer and Elite Rider, and can heal.<br />
Four copies of Aragorn mean he can exert with the bow and still expect him not to be exausted. It&#39;s nice to look at opponents hand, that&#39;s why 2 Stings. Also moria is pretty big here, 2 paths and 2 fortresses along with bow and firefoot usually handle it.<br />
<br />
Shadow is my first attempt with Uruk archers. Denial can be a problem, power is for that. Also tower is nice. Could put Desert Lords in (if I had any). Lurtz is fierce, If it dies in aimed archery, still ok, that&#39;s three wounds. Noone expects a pump, savagery is very nice. It lets some of the archers win their skirmishes.<br />
DH can be a problem, since there are quite a few conditions and events, and those pesky hobbitses can take a lot of wounds.<br />
